OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1775578269
OL,3,CThree new railway stations open to the
OL,4,Cpublic for the first time
OL,6,FThe Camp Hill Line was closed in 1941
OL,7,Fduring the Second World War due to
OL,8,Fcoal shortages, and each new station
OL,9,Fhas been built on its original site.
OL,11,FThe stations will be operated by West
OL,12,FMidlands Railway (WMR) and connect
OL,13,Fpassengers to Birmingham New Street
OL,14,Fand Kings Norton.
OL,16,FThe line will have the newest diesel
OL,17,Ffleet, the Class 196s, which first
OL,18,Fentered service in 2022.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/5
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
